   <mods:abstract>She asks Jay's friendly interposition and influence on behalf of her
            family and recounts in detail their recent difficulties in trying to change their
            residence to a healthier climate for her ailing brother. She particularly requests that
            Jay write a note to General Gates, if he thinks it will do any good, requesting that the
            Bayards be allowed to pass beyond Ludlow's Landing and not be forced to remain for
            another eight or more days abroad the sloop on which they have been travelling from Fish
            Kill to Poughkeepsie and lately to Ludlow's Landing.</mods:abstract>
